1281"}, {"t": "Just a Gigolo", "c": "Leonello Casucci", "w": "69250"}]}, {"id": "10836", "date": "1976-02-13", "label": "Benny Goodman, Clarinet", "venue": "Main Hall", "roles": ["cornet"], "works": [{"t": "Strike Up the Band: The Man I Love", "c": "George Gershwin", "w": "24608"}, {"t": "Avalon", "c": "Vincent Rose", "w": "50930"}, {"t": "One O'Clock Jump", "c": "Count Basie", "w": "15359"}, {"t": "Calamity Jane: Secret Love", "c": "Sammy Fain", "w": "62761"}, {"t": "Swingin’ the Dream: Darn that Dream", "c": "Jimmy Van Heusen", "w": "20484"}, {"t": "After You've Gone", "c": "Turner Layton", "w": "21325"}, {"t": "Don't Be That Way", "c": "Edgar Sampson", "w": "7484"}, {"t": "One O'Clock Jump", "c": "Count Basie", "w": "15359"}, {"t": "On Green Dolphin Street", "c": "Bronislaw Kaper", "w": "55739"}]}], "works_created": [], "quotes": [], "about_quotes": [{"speaker": "Kenny Davern", "relation": "knows of", "confidence": 1.0, "evidence": "he asked them well, “How did Louis Armstrong influence you?” So everybody, like Miles Davis says... And when he got to Bobby Hackett he said how did he influence you, and he says, “Well,” he says, with that New England accent he says, “Well I spent half my life,” he says, “stealing everything I coul", "doc_title": "Kenny Davern interviewed by Michael Woods, Clinton, New York, September 23, 1995 [interview 1 of 2]", "collection": "hamilton", "url": "https://litsdigital.hamilton.edu/collections/object/kenny-davern-interviewed-michael-woods-clinton-new-york-september-23-1995"}, {"speaker": "Budd Johnson", "relation": "knows of", "confidence": 1.0, "evidence": "[INTERVIEWER] Bobby Hackett and I the other night tried to remember Benny Harris' name and it came up two days later.", "doc_title": "68515_Budd Johnson oral history interview", "collection": "rutgers", "url": "https://rucore.libraries.rutgers.edu/rutgers-lib/68515/"}, {"speaker": "Cliff Leeman", "relation": "knows of", "confidence": 1.0, "evidence": "He was mostly known for his baritone playing, all the records he made with Bobby Hackett and in that era.", "doc_title": "68087_Cliff Leeman oral history interview", "collection": "rutgers", "url": "https://rucore.libraries.rutgers.edu/rutgers-lib/68087/"}, {"speaker": "Henry A. \"Hank\" Kmen", "relation": "played with", "confidence": 1.0, "evidence": "I later, but not too much later, played with Bobby myself. Played in his bands, both big and little.", "doc_title": "Henry A. \"Hank\" Kmen Interview, 1963-02-13", "collection": "tulane", "url": "https://library.search.tulane.edu/permalink/01TUL_INST/4h6sc4/alma9945523779806326"}, {"speaker": "Michael Moore", "relation": "played with", "confidence": 1.0, "evidence": "And Bobby Hackett — I actually met Bobby Hackett and played with him at that time.", "doc_title": "Michael Moore interviewed by Monk Rowe, Chautauqua, New York, September 12, 1997", "collection": "hamilton", "url": "https://litsdigital.hamilton.edu/collections/object/michael-moore-interviewed-monk-rowe-chautauqua-new-york-september-12-1997"}, {"speaker": "John Altman", "relation": "knows of", "confidence": 1.0, "evidence": "He also was jamming with Bunny Berigan and Bobby Hackett and Bud Freeman.", "doc_title": "John Altman interviewed by Monk Rowe, via Zoom, September 14, 2023", "collection": "hamilton", "url": "https://litsdigital.hamilton.edu/collections/object/john-altman-interviewed-monk-rowe-zoom-september-14-2023"}]}